I'm always delighted when a loon suddenly 'appears' near the boat. The brief moments of companionship only enhance the beauty and solitude of a sunset on a favorite northern lake.

In this dramatic image, ownership of the corn field is briefly contested between man and the ring-necked pheasants. The farmer means no harm, and on this fall evening wishes only to use the land on a temporary basis. He will soon willingly relinquish the territory to the wildlife and, as payment for the disturbance, offer the harvest leftovers.

“Dawn is breaking as the canoe-topped sedan and trailer loaded with decoys chugs up to Leslie's Blacksmith Shop and Sports Store. Earlier arrivals, a friendly combination of farmers in their bib overalls and town folk in fancier outfits, are already warming up around the glowing forge. Terry Redlin fondly remembers scenes such as this from his boyhood. Leslie was a local entrepreneur who expanded his farm into a blacksmith service, then to a cafe wrap-around on his barn, and finally to cabins along the stream for overnight guests. Terry especially recalls the clank of the hammer and pungent aroma of hot metal.”

column1: TRANQUIL WATERS—WHITETAIL DEER;  MASTER ARTISAN COLLECTION — ARTIST PROOF EDITION (AP) ART COLLECTION
column4: As a gentle autumn fog lifts from the riverbank and in the valley, a whitetail buck and doe enjoy the tranquility of their surroundings. The only sounds to be heard are the gentle splashing of the river as the pair move upstream. It was my intent to have shades of foggy greens and grays create a tranquil mood.

In this delightful image we remember a time when the world was a symphony of youthful shouts, glorious blue skies and secret hideaways in the trees. On such carefree days friends gathered to test their homemade kites against the brisk spring breeze. The kites soar high and free, not at the end of new-fangled nylon line, but securely controlled by thick cotton string. The string has broken many times but is easily fixed, the knots' bulky presence visible even at this distance.

In this nostalgic scene 'coming home' becomes a place and a feeling. It speaks to us of a tradition we share, if not in actual fact, then in the values it represents. The Christmas tree has been cut from just down the road. We can imagine the fresh smells of baking bread in the kitchen. The farm house will soon be alive with the joyful sounds of children from two generations. And the pole signs in front of the barn tell us there are other farms nearby where similar preparations are underway.

Choose from panoramic horizontal crop from the Horizons Collection or oval image. Both are open edition prints. Horizons image size, 8-1/2" x 27". Oval image size, 12" x 16".

“All animals are curious. Deer are especially cautious, too. On this quiet summer day, Terry Redlin remembers the behavior of animals he watched in the fields as a kid. The rail fence serves as a protector for both the fawn and the colt, allowing them the safety in which to satisfy their curiosity. The doe, knowing all is well in front, turns her head to watch for predators. Note the small trio of wildflower blooms in the foreground. Nature has found the perfect protected spot for these wayward seeds to flourish.”

Limited edition of 9,500 signed and numbered art prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 2 framing options. (Artist proof available.) Elite open edition print. Image size, 14" x 24". My husband and I had just returned from a November hunt in New Mexico and inspired by the beauty of that area this painting was created.

Open edition from the Great Northern Art Premium Framed Prints Collection. Image size, 17" x 23". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

“On this peaceful winter evening, a 1930’s vintage sedan with headlights ablaze has finally reached its destination. The occupants will be visiting with old friends in the cabin. Nestled on the bluff the deer quietly watch, both part of and apart from the whole experience.”

Legacy canvas edition of 500 signed and numbered canvases. Image size, 22" x 37". Available framed.

The Great Eight - Whitetail Deer painting is perfect for anyone looking to add some character to a rustic or traditional interior, the remarkable detail of the design will instill a natural touch to any space it’s in. For the hunting fanatics among you the Great Eight - Whitetail Deer painting is an absolute must-have as it’s an original Michael Sieve, a wildlife artist who captures the essence of the outdoors as he’s worked on farms and hunted since he was a child - this essence can be seen throughout the design. “Many whitetail bucks are eight pointers when they are young. A few have only eight points when they reach maturity. Fewer still grow very large impressive racks as mature eight-pointers. Those that do are called 'Great Eights.'”

“The fields have yielded a bumper crop this fall and the local grain elevator is crowded with trucks and trailers waiting their turn to unload. After a long and tiring day, the farmers are anxious to get home, but they also welcome this chance to relax for a moment with a cup of hot coffee, chat about crop prices, and trade the latest gossip.”

column1: FOR PURPLE MOUNTAIN MAJESTIES ART COLLECTION
column4:
“The opening of the west was not all long hours and hard work. There were also times of leisure, especially for the young, and what could be more spectacular than a playground in the shadows of the majestic Tetons. Spring has arrived and the snow is retreating up the mountain slopes. Flowers are blooming and in the distance elk move out of sheltered valleys to higher ground.”

Third in the America the Beautiful series. Limited edition of 29,500 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 16-1/2" x 28-3/8". Artist proof edition of 2,950 signed and numbered prints. This painting follows the painting Northern Light-Loons showing the family together later in the fall. The chick has matured and is capable of migration now.

Limited edition of 1,200 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 10-1/2" x 31-1/2". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

The neighborhood is aglow with lights as families prepare for the holiday season. Mom has the tree decorated and lit. From the window, she sees a car slowly pull up to the front walk. She opens the door, expecting to embrace her son, but is horrified to see a representative from the Navy and a Chaplain walking up the steps. Our hearts sink as we realize it is not her son, but the devastating news that he has been killed in war. This painting immerses us in the pain of this American family's ultimate loss. This series is a tribute to the memory of Terry Redlin's brother-in-law and good friend Charles Langenfeld. Charles, a Navy Hospital Corpman, was killed in the Siege of Khe Sanh during the Vietnam War in 1968. Like many Americans, Terry's family lives forever with the pain of the ultimate loss.

Available in three edition and image sizes. Limited edition of 3,500 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from two frame options. (Artist proof also available.) In the Flying Free painting, we see “Terry Redlin’s first painting of the American Bald Eagle, we see not the traditional format of a solitary bird, but a family high in the western mountains building toward its own bright future.” An original piece by one the country’s most celebrated wildlife artists, Terry Redlin, this painting perfectly captures the majesty of the wilderness - bold mountains, crystal clear waters and lush forestry. The Flying Free painting encapsulates what makes our country great - unrivaled beauty and a free spirit!

column1: THE WAITING GAME—DEER HUNTING ART COLLECTION
column4:
Displaying fortitude, hunters often confront difficult situations. Here a great trophy is out of range from the bowhunter's tree stand. If the hunter shoots, he may miss the shot, wound the animal and leave it suffering. If the hunter decides to wait, perhaps in a few minutes or even another day a better shot will come.

From the "Art of Hunting" series. Available in limited print edition of 2,500 signed and numbered art prints or premier giclee canvas edition of 95 signed and numbered canvases. Print image size, 16" x 29-1/2". Canvas image size, 21" x 38-1/2". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

I was in awe of the determination and brut strength of these rutting elk. Pushing each other this way and that, kicking up dust, and scarring each other. I was exhausted just watching them. It seemed the ultimate example of doing anything for love.

Limited edition of 450 art prints. Image size, 16"H x 20"W. Framed size, 27"H x 31"W with 2" brown moulding. Double matting with soft white outer mat. Published exclusively by Wild Wings®. Printed and framed in the USA.

“It is early spring and the local lakeside general store is open and ready for the season. From fishing lures to homemade ice cream, the local store is packed full of all the necessities of lake living. Soon the city folk will begin to arrive to spend their summer vacation on the peaceful shores of the crystal clear lake. The store owner is raising the flag as he does every morning and the children are ready for a fun day of fishing. The birds are singing and the water is calm—it is a perfect spring day.”

Limited edition of 9,500 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 3 framing options. Artist proof edition of 950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Elite open edition art print. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 5 framing options.

“It’s that magical moment in the deep woods when the morning sun first slices through the thick underbrush to cover the landscape with its warm rays. The camper, an early riser, has loaded his fishing gear into the old wooden canoe and with his best buddy is headed out to catch breakfast. A few minutes downstream is a secluded lake, which, in this version of the story, is home to an ample supply of four to five pounders. High in the distant sky a flight of Canadas have also begun their daily search for food. And back near the tree line whitetail deer, a buck and two does, apparently unthreatened by the visitors, quietly observe the action.”

column1: MISTY MORNING—PINTOS;  MASTER ARTISAN COLLECTION — STANDARD NUMBERED EDITION (SN) ART COLLECTION
column4: Early morning fog from the Willamette River is slowly lifting as the three pintos gallop across their pasture. Thriving in the cool September morning, the pintos embrace the open plain and light mist found in the valley, before the September sun rises fully.

“These young fishermen come well equipped with fishing gear. Some sit on the bank watching patiently for the first nibble. Others relax in the shade amid a golden field of dandelions. Across the stream two Canada geese herd their brood to the water's edge. They are undisturbed by all the activity, having learned long ago to share this idyllic location with their human friends.”

Artist proof edition of 950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Master Canvas edition of 1,950 signed and numbered canvases. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Encore II open edition print. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18".

When I am out in the natural world, I can stop to find many wild creatures in one small area. I love to bow hunt and I'm a quiet observer of all the wonderful things that take place in the woods. In my painting 'Seven Critters', there is a chickadee, red squirrel, pileated woodpecker, meadow vole, and three deer. So next time you are out in creation, don't just drive through it, but rather stop to be the quiet observer, and you will see so much more.

Framed with a Contemporary framing selection of a 4" single white mat and 1" charcoal wood-finished moulding. Framed image size, 21" x 26" Published exclusively by Wild Wings. a division of Art Brand Studios, LLC.

“In this peaceful scene the children excitedly point out the mallards flying low overhead. The proud Belgians, the warmly bundled family, the crisp country air and the fading sun all convey the essential meaning of ‘the pleasures of winter.’ We are reminded of a more innocent time when the countryside was at peace with itself and traditional family values reigned.”

2011 Holiday edition of 2011 numbered prints with printed remarque in lower left corner. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 3 framing options. Also available; Encore open edition art print. “I have always had an interest in the history and culture of Native Americans. These are all Lakota Sioux.“

LImited edition of 250 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 16-1/2" x 22". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

“On this magical winter evening, the wind is still and the temperature mild enough for kids to fashion both snowmen and snow forts. As Mom and Dad begin a sleigh ride, their daughter points the way. Or has she just released a playful snowball? In either case, we are presented with a true ‘winter wonderland’ and the beginning of beautiful new memories.”

Encore II open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18". Choose from 5 framing options.

The ring-necked pheasant is very much at home in overgrown fencerows found all across heartland America. Outdated farm machinery is often abandoned in these fields. It is in just such a setting that I chose to portray these two wary roosters.

column1: FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL—BLACK LAB PUPPY ART COLLECTION
column4:
After the success of 'Quack Attack',people kept asking for it in a black lab. So I did one better. I wanted the story to continue, and I came up with this idea. I thought of a black lab all excited on his first day of school, new hat, new shoes and of course, lunch box in tow! Personalized with his own 'Quack Attack' experience.

Signature edition. Image size, 12" x 14". A Wild Wings exclusive.

“While taking an early morning drive I was inspired to create this painting after seeing a pair of deer at the edge of a plowed field.”

Limited edition of 950 signed and numbered art prints. Image size, 16-1/2" x 25". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.
Framed, limited edition of 250 signed and numbered art prints of the eyes of a puma. Published exclusively by Wild Wings. Print size is 8"H x 23.5"W. Choice frame size is 18"H x 33.5"W.

The spectacular waterways of the Pacific Northwest inspired me to paint this bald eagle. I wanted to instill in the viewer a sense of power both in the beat of the eagles wings and of the pounding waters of the falls beyond.

Limited edition of 1,200 signed and numbered prints made from the original acrylic painting. Image size, 25" x 17". Framed size 38" x 30" with 3-3/8" espresso-finished moulding with gold edges. Double matting with loam (dark brown) outer mat and brass nameplate. Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

column1: HEART OF THE TIMBER—MALLARDS ART COLLECTION
column4:
“Stuttgart, Arkansas is widely known as the duck hunting capitol of the world. Countless numbers of ducks and geese congregate in the rice fields and flooded timber forests near Stuttgart during the fall and winter months. The mallards depicted here are pitching into the heart of one of these timber areas.”

Limited edition of 750 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 16-1/2" x 25".

I've been fascinated by those magical days when an early morning fog is pierced by the morning sun. It had been several years planning to do a painting showing this dramatic setting. As luck would have it, at the very time I started this painting, one of those beautiful days came along to further inspire me.

Beautiful artwork that stands out from the rest! Our new Framed Illusions line features dimensional art created by layers of printing on glass and paper. Framed size, 16"H x 16"W with 2" walnut or cream colored wood moulding. Published exclusively by Wild Wings®. Printed and framed in the USA.

column1: WATERFOWLING HOT SPOTS; GREEN—WINGED TEAL ART COLLECTION
column4:
Duck hunters across the nation know the Platte River area of south central Nebraska as a real 'hot spot' for waterfowl. The green-winged teal, while being the smallest of the ducks, is also one of the fastest flyers. This flock of green-wings is zig-zagging along the Platte, looking for the ideal landing spot.

Artist proof edition of 250 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 16-1/2" x 25". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

column1: WHAT WILL MOM SAY? ART COLLECTION
column4:
I was originally approached by a customer to do a commission. She initiated the idea of a dog loosing its spots like Gesundheit" and having to go home not sure how to explain it. I found the photo which I thought would work and the rest is history."

Signature edition. Image size, 8" x 16". A Wild Wings exclusive.

column1: BLACK ATTACK—GOOSE STRIKES BACK ART COLLECTION
column4:
I actually did this painting first. I saw the goose doing his thing first and it was at this point the sequel for 'Quack Attack/Strikes Back' came into plan. The request for was pretty strong and I thought this would complete the set.

Signature open edition. Image size, 12" x 14-1/4". A Wild Wings exclusive.

“The open prairies of the Southern Black Hills provided the setting for these mature bulls who separate themselves from the rest of the herd during the months of summer.”

Open edition framed art print from the Great Northern Art Premium Collection.

column1: TRANQUIL WATERS—WHITETAIL DEER;  MASTER ARTISAN COLLECTION — ARTIST PROOF EDITION (AP) ART COLLECTION
column4: As a gentle autumn fog lifts from the riverbank and in the valley, a whitetail buck and doe enjoy the tranquility of their surroundings. The only sounds to be heard are the gentle splashing of the river as the pair move upstream. It was my intent to have shades of foggy greens and grays create a tranquil mood.

Isolated from the pack the lone survivor makes his own way, independent, strong and noble! Visually powerful in every detail; a striking sculpture for desk or shelf. Cold cast and hand painted. Open edition. 6-1/4"L x 12"H x 5"D.

column1: FOR PURPLE MOUNTAIN MAJESTIES ART COLLECTION
column4:
“The opening of the west was not all long hours and hard work. There were also times of leisure, especially for the young, and what could be more spectacular than a playground in the shadows of the majestic Tetons. Spring has arrived and the snow is retreating up the mountain slopes. Flowers are blooming and in the distance elk move out of sheltered valleys to higher ground.”

Third in the America the Beautiful series. Limited edition of 29,500 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 16-1/2" x 28-3/8". Artist proof edition of 2,950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 16-1/2" x 28-3/8". Encore canvas open edition. Canvas size, 14" x 24". Open edition pencil sketch print. Image size, 8" x 10". Open edition linen art prints. Image size, 7-3/4" x 13-3/4".

“Whitetail deer, a favorite subject for my painting, was a natural subject when I was exploring the small stream area that had recently flooded due to heavy fall rains. The small grassy island presented the composition element I was looking for.”

Limited edition of 450 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 16" x 24". Framed size, 28-1/2" x 36-1/2" with 2-3/4" distressed walnut finish moulding. Triple matting with suede oak brown outer mat. A Wild Wings exclusive. Made in the USA!

Watson is hot on the trail of his next case, following his nose to solve whodunit in "The Case of the Missing Biscuit".

Open edition of 11" x 14" art prints are the perfect size to fill a smaller space in your home. Unframed. Published exclusively by Art Brand Studios. Made in USA.

The Autumn Evening painting will instill a calming atmosphere in any room it’s featured in with its rich shades of hazel, blue and green “As entire families prepare their lawns for winter, the sweet smell of burning leaves permeates the air. I remember those autumn evenings as youthful contests. How big and bright could you make the fire? And how many times could you jump through the flames and smoke before a nearby adult called a halt to the fun.` The Autumn Evening painting makes you think of simpler times and will act as a relaxing focal point to any living room or bedroom.

“The annual mating ritual of moose includes bulls challenging each other for the right to mate with the cows. This painting expresses the essence (or, shows the culmination) of a successful challenge.”

Limited edition of 450 signed and numbered art prints made from the original acrylic painting. Image size, 17" x 28". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

Open edition from the Great Northern Art Premium Collection. Image size, 17" x 23". Choose from two framing options; regular premium framing and premium plus framing. A Wild Wings exclusive. Great Northern Art images may be available in various print lines.

column1: A WEALTH OF FIELD FLOWERS ART COLLECTION
column4:
A dear friend of our surprised us with this beautiful bouquet of meadow flowers. Such plentiful richness for a vase! Poppies unfortunately don't last very long in a vase so I will have to paint these flowers quickly before they wilt. But once I immortalize these flowers on my watercolor paper they will last forever! --Marjolein Bastin.

Open edition of 11" x 14" art prints are the perfect size to fill a smaller space in your home. Published exclusively by Art Brand Studios. Made in USA.

“It has been a day filled with deep satisfactions. No other camper has been sighted. The deer trail discovered back in the woods led to a hidden spring. A grouse was flushed from the aspen thicket. The wild call of the loon trivialized all human sounds. Now, as the day’s activity turns to quiet reflection, Canada geese swoop low as if to say goodnight.”

Encore open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18". Choose from 6 framing options.

The deer have found an ideal location to spend a few peaceful hours. The exposed grass offers some protection from the wet snow, the warm sun is unobstructed, the river bottom is nearby and there is no sign of man's presence. They will rest for a while more, then move on in their continuing quest for browse.

Open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Part of the Horizons Collection of horizontal, open edition art prints, excerpted from previous Redlin print releases. Image size, 8-1/2" x 27". Choose from 5 framing options.

column4: “After a night’s hunt, a young cougar makes her way through the mountain terrain past the rhododendron and lupines to a welcoming cool watering hole.”

column1: GREETING THE NEW DAY—CARDINAL ART COLLECTION
column4: Simply brilliant! Applying a less is more approach, beautiful artwork is presented as the distinctive focal point in our Contempo Square Art Collection. Open edition by artist Susan Bourdet. Image size, 12"H x 12"W. Framed size, 24"H x 24"W with 2" moulding and single white mat. Published by Wild Wing; a division of Art Brand Studios, LLC.

The three Shades of Gray" paintings show a whitetail buck in the place he calls home at three different times during the fall, and at different times of the day. In "White," it is late fall or early winter. The stress and rigor of the rut have left this buck tired and hungry. If he is to survive, he will have no choice but to move into the fields to feed in order to restore his lost body weight."

Limited edition of 950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 17-1/2" x 14".

column1: SUNRISE AT THE WATER—LEOPARD ART COLLECTION
column4: Limited edition of 25 signed and numbered canvas art prints. Available framed and unframed. Published exclusively by Wild Wings. Image size: 18"H x 24"W

“These young fishermen come well equipped with fishing gear. Some sit on the bank watching patiently for the first nibble. Others relax in the shade amid a golden field of dandelions. Across the stream two Canada geese herd their brood to the water's edge. They are undisturbed by all the activity, having learned long ago to share this idyllic location with their human friends.”

Artist proof edition of 950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Master Canvas edition of 1,950 signed and numbered canvases. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Encore II open edition print. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18".

“Creating a flower garden is like painting with living palette of colors. The garden provides inspiration for my paintings, especially when nature provides her own touches. Foxglove and delphinium are hummingbird favorites, sure to attract my favorite subject.”

Limited edition of 950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 30-1/2" x 10". A Wild Wings exclusive.

“The heavy frost glistens in the morning light. Winter is in the air. The icy coating is a precursor to the snow that will soon blanket the surroundings. As the horse-drawn wagon and its passengers leave the church and cross the covered bridge, only the dog knows the young boy is hiding there. As he crouches out of sight of the grown-ups, he is praying that he will not be discovered. He knows that with one bark, his secret will be revealed.”

Elite open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from two moulding options (walnut or oak) and two matting options (regular or deluxe suede mats). Also available; open edition Encore canvas print. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from two framing options.

“The deserted crossroads elevator was once at the center of a thriving farm community. It now stands mute, a victim of man’s progress. In the foreground freshly stacked hay bales seem to mock, in both form and substance, the abandoned elevator. Their presence indicates man still occupies the land, but with a new set of priorities. The only witnesses to this transition are the calmly feeding pheasants.”

Open edition art print from the Image size, 20-1/4" x 11-1/2". Choose from 4 framing options.

This is a typical canoe-in camp scene in the Boundary Waters of northern Minnesota. The evening camp is ready and soon fresh walleye will be sizzling on the campfire. Limited edition of 1,325 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 17" x 27"

A Wild Wings exclusive.

column1: OLD LOGGER'S TRAIL—RUFFED GROUSE ART COLLECTION
column4:
“Winding through the trees with the sun breaking on their backs, a pair of grouse takes advantage of the clearing made by early loggers. This painting was created from an actual scene near the artist’s cabin.”

Encore open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 8-3/4" x 14". Choose from 6 framing options.

“As the geese head for the cornfield behind the farmhouse, only the beating of their wings breaks the silence. The farmer has paused for supper, too, and down at the dock the fishing gear waits for him to try his luck before the sun goes down. Even the pets reflect the slower pace of life on the farm once the chores are done. This absence of activity is temporary, of course. The hunting dogs know that their busy season is approaching, and watch the passing geese with alert anticipation.”

Limited edition of 9,500 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 16-1/2" x 28-1/2". (Artist proof available.) Recieve a FREE companion sketch when you order the limited edition print! “Autumn leaves rest gently on the milkhouse roof and tractor hood while the children have begun their morning chores. Suddenly the silence is broken as five mallards fly low through the trees. In startled surprise the children and pets look up to catch a fleeting glance. In a blink all is again silent and the business of the day will continue. Only the windmill’s rotating squeak is heard as water cools the fresh milk stored in the pump house.”

Elite open edition art print. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 5 framing options. Also available; Museum Canvas open edition (image size, 23" x 39-1/2") and Companion prints (image sizes, 8" x 8").

column4: Limited edition of 100 signed and numbered art prints and 100 signed and numbered canvas prints by Guy Hobbs. Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

The spirit of sharing is beautifully extended to the world of nature in this holiday scene. To help wildlife survive the winter, the farmer has temptingly placed two corn shocks at the open side of his house. A welcoming wreath hangs near the door for human visitors. And a Christmas tree warmly beckons in the window as two late-leaving mallards glide down for a needed meal.

2013 Holiday Print; signed open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 14" x 22". Choose from 3 framing options. Also available; smaller sized Encore II open edition print. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18". Choose from 6 framing options.

The ghost of a barn fades into view through the fog behind them. Image size, 24" x 18". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

“I love to paint reflective surfaces, so finding this beautiful farm with a creek running right past was a great discovery. My wife and children seem to be ‘reflecting’ as well, and a winter campfire is the perfect place to recall a wonderful winter day.”

Limited edition of 850 signed and numbered art prints made from the original painting. Image size, 13-1/2" x 32". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.
